articles.description: Nick Mayo scored 18 points, grabbed five rebounds and blocked four shots and Eastern Kentucky made 4 of 6 foul shots down the stretch to hold off Morehead State 75-73 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: E. Kentucky holds off Morehead St.; Mayo scores 18 PTs

articles.description: Tyler Sharpe hit two 3-pointers in the closing minutes Saturday night to secure Northern Kentucky's fifth straight win, an 86-80 victory over Green Bay that moved the Norse into sole possession of first-place in the Horizon League.
articles.headline: Northern Kentucky takes Horizon lead, beats Green Bay 86-80

articles.description: John Dewey III stole an inbound pass and fed Christopher Galbreath Jr. for a layup in the final seconds as Sam Houston State took a 71-69 win over Lamar in Southland Conference play on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Sam Houston St. slips past Lamar 71-69 in final seconds

articles.description: Big Green holds off Princeton to pick up its first #RoadtoIvyMadness victory of the year
articles.headline: Dartmouth picks up first Ivy win of the season  - Via Ivy League

images.caption: Big Green holds off Princeton to pick up its first #RoadtoIvyMadness victory of the year
images.name: Dartmouth picks up first Ivy win of the season  - Via Ivy League

articles.description: Zane Waterman tossed in 28 points, Zavier Turner scored 25 and Pauly Paulicap chipped in with a double-double to propel Manhattan to a 93-76 victory over Monmouth on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Waterman, Turner lead Manhattan over Monmouth 93-76

articles.description: Denzel Mahoney had 27 points, including a game-tying 3-pointer at the end of regulation, and Southeast Missouri State beat Tennessee-Martin 81-77 in overtime on Saturday night.
articles.headline: SE Missouri State beats Tenn.-Martin 81-77 in OT

videos.description: Galin Smith loses his man on the screen and gets wide open for the two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Smith gets open for Bama dunk

videos.description: Tremont Waters finds Brandon Sampson on the fast-break for an alley-oop.
videos.headline: Waters hits Sampson for LSU alley-oop

videos.description: Daryl Edwards takes advantage of a pass that deflects off an official and goes his way for a fast-break dunk.
videos.headline: Edwards dunks off lucky bounce for Tigers

videos.description: Collin Sexton fakes out his man with a fake behind-the-back pass in stride and misses the layup but Alex Reese gets a putback to go for the Tide.
videos.headline: Sexton fakes behind-the back for Bama

videos.description: Daniel Giddens follows up a missed shot and crashes in for a putback dunk.
videos.headline: Giddens slams home putback for the Tide

videos.description: Galin Smith follows up a missed layup with a big putback dunk over LSU defenders.
videos.headline: Bama's Smith hammers putback dunk

videos.description: Will Wade gets fired up on a kicked ball call on Tremont Waters late in the 2nd half against Alabama.
videos.headline: LSU head coach loses it on kick call

videos.description: Alabama goes a perfect 14-for-14 from the free throw line in the final 12 minutes to hold off a surging LSU and earn the win.
videos.headline: Bama uses efficient second half to put away LSU 74-66
